<subSubSection pageId="349" pageNumber="350" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="349" pageNumber="350">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="349" pageNumber="350">
This western species is found from south-central Alberta to Vancouver Island, north to the Skeena River drainage in central British Columbia (Lindroth 1963b: 305), south at least to central California in the Coast Ranges (Casey 1918: 53, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1868" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="349" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetragonoderum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="349" pageNumber="350">Bembidion tetragonoderum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and &quot;New Mexico&quot; (Hayward 1897: 61). The record from southeastern Wisconsin (Messer 2010: 36) needs confirmation since the specimen could be mislabeled.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
